# Image derivatives
Hx = [[1, -1]]
Hy = np.transpose(Hx)
Ix = sp.signal.convolve2d(img, Hx, mode='same')
Iy = sp.signal.convolve2d(img, Hy, mode='same')

plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.subplot(121)
plt.title('Ix')
plt.xlabel('x'), plt.ylabel('y')
plt.imshow(Ix, origin='lower', cmap='gray')

plt.title('Iy')
plt.xlabel('x'), plt.ylabel('y')
plt.imshow(Iy, origin='lower',cmap='gray');

# Visualizing gradient magnitude and direction using colors
Igrad = np.sqrt(np.square(Ix) + np.square(Iy))

Igrad_c = np.zeros([img.shape[0], img.shape[0],3], dtype=np.uint8)
Igrad_c[..., 1] = 255
mag, ang = cv.cartToPolar(Ix[...], Iy[...])
Igrad_c[..., 0] = ang * 180 / np.pi / 2
Igrad_c[..., 2] = cv.normalize(mag, None, 0, 255, cv.NORM_MINMAX)
Igrad_color = cv.cvtColor(Igrad_c, cv.COLOR_HSV2BGR)

plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
plt.subplot(121)
plt.imshow(Igrad, origin='lower', cmap='gray')
plt.subplot(122)
plt.imshow(Igrad_color, origin='lower', cmap=cm.get_cmap('prism'));
In [5]:
# IMPLEMENT compute_histograms method
def compute_histograms(img):
    # Hx = [[1, -1]]
    # Hy = np.transpose(Hx)
    # Ix = sp.signal.convolve2d(img, Hx, mode='same')
    # Iy = sp.signal.convolve2d(img, Hy, mode='same')
    Ix = cv.Sobel(img, cv.CV_64F, 1, 0, ksize=3)
    Iy = cv.Sobel(img, cv.CV_64F, 0, 1, ksize=3)

    Igrad = np.sqrt(np.power(Ix, 2) + np.power(Iy, 2))
    # Igrad = np.sqrt(np.square(Ix) + np.square(Iy))

    Iangle = np.arctan2(Iy, Ix)*(180.0/np.pi)
    
    Igrad_ = Igrad.ravel()
    Igrad_used = Igrad_[Igrad_ != 0.0]
    bins_grad = np.linspace(np.min(Igrad_used), np.max(Igrad_used), 33)
    h_grad1, edges = np.histogram(Igrad_used, bins_grad)
    c_grad1 = (edges[1:] + edges[:-1]) / 2

    Iangle_ = Iangle.ravel()
    Iangle_used = Iangle_[Iangle_ != 0.0]
    angle_bins = np.linspace(-180, 180, 361)
    h_angle1, edges = np.histogram(Iangle_used, angle_bins)
    c_angle1 = (edges[1:] + edges[:-1]) / 2
    
    return h_grad1, c_grad1, h_angle1, c_angle1

In [10]:
import collections

def compare_histograms(hist1, hist2):
    return True if collections.Counter(hist1) == collections.Counter(hist2) else False
